{"title_page": "Project Polaroid", "text_new": "{{Infobox album\n| name       = Project Polaroid\n| type       = studio\n| artist     = [[Kool Keith]] & TomC3\n| cover      = Kool_keith_and_tomc3-project_polaroid.jpg\n| alt        =\n| released   = April 25, 2006\n| recorded   = 2006\n| venue      =\n| studio     = {{hlist|The Closet (East)|The Closet (West)}}\n| genre      = {{hlist|[[Alternative hip hop]]|[[underground hip hop]]}}\n| length     = 46:53\n| label      = Threshold Recordings LLC\n| producer   = TomC3\n| chronology = [[Kool Keith]]\n| prev_title = [[Nogatco Rd.]]\n| prev_year  = 2006\n| next_title = [[The Return of Dr. Octagon]]\n| next_year  = 2006\n| misc       = {{Singles\n | name        = Project Polaroid\n | type        = studio\n | single1     = Digital Engineering/Diamond District\n | single1date = March 3, 2006\n}}\n}}\n'''''The Original SoundTrack Album of Project Polaroid''''' is the studio album by American [[Hip hop music|hip hop]] duo Project Polaroid, composed of [[The Bronx|New York]] rapper [[Kool Keith]] and [[San Francisco Bay Area|Bay Area]] producer TomC3. It was released worldwide on April 25, 2006 via Threshold Recordings<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/project-polaroid/id131747482|title=Project Polaroid by Kool Keith on Apple Music|website=[[iTunes]]|language=en-us|access-date=November 26, 2017}}</ref> and on June 28, 2006 in [[Japan]] via Swamp Records. Audio production of the project was entirely handled by TomC3, and featured guest appearances from [[Organized Konfusion]]'s [[Prince Po]], [[Masters of Illusion]]'s Motion Man, and [[Third Sight]]'s Roughneck Jihad. \n== Track listing ==\n{{Track listing\n| all_writing = \n| all_music = TomC3\n| title1 = Project Polaroid\n| length1 = 3:24\n| title2 = Space 8000\n| length2 = 3:38\n| title3 = Talk To The Romans\n| length3 = 3:06\n| title4 = Mechanical Mechanix\n| note4 = featuring [[Prince Po]]\n| length4 = 2:42\n| title5 = I\u2019m Libra\n| lengt