t&Include=Y&rid=1119 Library of Parliament &ndash; History of Federal Ridings since 1867:  Mount Royal]\n|- \n|}\n\n[[File:Yes check.svg|15px|Yes]] Elected. <br />\n'''X''' Incumbent.\n\n=== 1979 Federal Election: Mount Royal ===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" \n|+ [[1979 Canadian federal election|Federal Election, 1979]]: [[Mount Royal (electoral district)|Mount Royal]], Quebec\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Party\n!Candidate!!Popular Vote!! % \n|-\n{{Canadian party colour|CA|Liberal|row-name}} \n||[[File:Yes check.svg|15px|Yes]] '''X''' [[Pierre Trudeau]]||align=center|43,202||align=center|85.2%\n|-\n{{Canadian party colour|CA|PC|row}}\n|[[Progressive Conservative Party of Canada|Progressive Conservative]]||J. David Dejong||align=center|3,660||align=center|7.2%\n|-\n{{Canadian party colour|CA|NDP|row}}\n|[[New Democratic Party]]||David C. Winch||align=center|2,023||align=center|4.0%\n|-\n{{Canadian party colour|CA|Social Credit|row-name}}\n|Lafl\u00e8che Trudeau||align=center|1,049||align=center|2.1%\n|-\n{{Canadian party colour|CA|Rhinoceros (historical)|row-name}}\n|[[Jacques Ferron]]||align=center|649||align=center|1.3%\n|-\n{{Canadian party colour|CA|Communist|row-name}}\n|David G. Johnston||align=center|81||align=center|0.2%\n|-\n{{Canadian party colour|CA|Marxist-Leninist|row-name}}\n|Robert Verrier||align=center|61||align=center|0.1%\n|-\n! colspan=3 align=center|Total!! align=right|50,725!! align=right|100.1%<sup>1</sup>\n|-\n| align=\"center\" colspan=5|'''Source:''' [https://lop.parl.ca/About/Parliament/FederalRidingsHistory/hfer.asp?Language=E&Search=Det&Include=Y&rid=1119 Library of Parliament &ndash; History of Federal Ridings since 1867:  Mount Royal]\n|- \n|}\n\n[[File:Yes check.svg|15px|Yes]] Elected. <br />\n'''X''' Incumbent. <br />\n<sup>1</sup> Rounding error.\n\n=== 1980 Federal Election: Mount Royal ===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" \n|+ [[1980 Canadian federal election|Federal Election, 1980]]: [[Mount Royal (electoral district)|Mount Royal]], Quebec\n|-\n!cols