ction: Mount Royal ===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" \n|+ [[1980 Canadian federal election|Federal Election, 1980]]: [[Mount Royal (electoral district)|Mount Royal]], Quebec\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Party\n!Candidate!!Popular Vote!! % \n|-\n{{Canadian party colour|CA|Liberal|row-name}} \n||[[File:Yes check.svg|15px|Yes]] '''X''' [[Pierre Trudeau]]||align=center|33,821||align=center|81.2%\n|-\n{{Canadian party colour|CA|PC|row}}\n|[[Progressive Conservative Party of Canada|Progressive Conservative]]||Harry Bloomfield||align=center|4,402||align=center|10.6%\n|-\n{{Canadian party colour|CA|NDP|row}}\n|[[New Democratic Party]]||David C. Winch||align=center|2,356||align=center|5.7%\n|-\n{{Canadian party colour|CA|Rhinoceros (historical)|row-name}}\n|Michel Flybin Rivard||align=center|715||align=center|1.7%\n|-\n{{Canadian party colour|CA|Independent|row}}\n|Independent||Gordon Edwards||align=center|149||align=center|0.4%\n|-\n{{Canadian party colour|CA|Libertarian|row-name}}\n|Paul Eddie||align=center|126||align=center|0.3%\n|-\n{{Canadian party colour|CA|Marxist-Leninist|row-name}}\n|Liz Watkins||align=center|68||align=center|0.2%\n|-\n! colspan=3 align=center|Total!! align=right|41,637!! align=right|100.1%<sup>1</sup>\n|-\n| align=\"center\" colspan=5|'''Source:''' [https://lop.parl.ca/About/Parliament/FederalRidingsHistory/hfer.asp?Language=E&Search=Det&Include=Y&rid=1119 Library of Parliament &ndash; History of Federal Ridings since 1867:  Mount Royal]\n|- \n|}\n\n[[File:Yes check.svg|15px|Yes]] Elected. <br />\n'''X''' Incumbent. <br />\n<sup>1</sup> Rounding error.\n\n== Liberal Party leadership convention, 1968 ==\n\n{{About||more detailed information about the 1968 Liberal leadership convention|Liberal Party of Canada leadership election, 1968}}\n\nTrudeau won the leadership on the fourth ballot.  His main opponents were [[Paul Hellyer]] and [[Robert Winters]], both former ministers in Pearson's governments.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+ Liberal Leadership Convention, April 6, 1968 <br /> Voting results by ballot\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\" colspan=\"2\" | Candidate \n!colspan = \"2\"|First Ballot \n!colspan = \"2\" |Second Ballot\n!colspan = \"2\" |Third Ballot\n!colspan = \"2\" |Fourth Ballot\n|-\n! Votes cast \n! %\n! Votes cast \n! %\n! Votes cast \n! %\n! Votes cast \n! %\n|- style=\"background:#EA6D6A\"\n|[[File:Pierre Trudeau (1975).jpg|50px]]\n|'''[[Pierre Trudeau]]'''\n|align = \"center\"|'''752'''\n|align = \"center\"|'''31.8%'''\n|align = \"center\"|'''964'''\n|align = \"center\"|'''40.8%'''\n|align = \"center\"|'''1051'''\n|align = \"center\"|'''44.6%'''\n|align = \"center\"|'''1,203'''\n|align = \"center\"|'''51.1%'''\n|-\n\n|[[File:Paul Hellyer-c1969.jpg|50px]]\n|[[Paul Hellyer]]\n|align = \"center\"|330\n|align = \"center\"|13.9%\n|align = \"center\"|465\n|align = \"center\"|19.7%\n|align = \"center\"|<br /><br /><br />377 <br /> '''<small>Withdrew after third ballot.</small>'''\n|align = \"center\"|16.0%\n|align = \"center\"|&ndash;\n|align = \"center\"|&ndash;\n|-\n\n|[[File:Robert Winters.jpg|50px]]\n|[[Robert Winters]]\n|align = \"center\"|293\n|align = \"center\"|12.4%\n|align = \"center\"|473\n|align = \"center\"|20.0%\n|align = \"center\"|621\n|align = \"center\"|26.3%\n|align = \"center\"|954\n|align = \"center\"|40.6%\n|-\n\n|[[File:John Turner by Gage Skidmore.jpg|50px]]\n|[[John Turner]]\n|align = \"center\"|277\n|align = \"center\"|11.7%\n|align = \"center\"|347\n|align = \"center\"|14.7%\n|align = \"center\"|279\n|align = \"center\"|11.8%\n|align = \"center\"|195\n|align = \"center\"|8.3%\n|-\n\n|\n|[[Paul Martin Sr.]]\n|align = \"center\"|<br /><br /><br />277 <br /> '''<small>Withdrew after first ballot.</small>'''\n|align = \"center\"|11.7%\n|align = \"center\"|&ndash;\n|align = \"center\"|&ndash;\n|align = \"center\"|&ndash;\n|align = \"center\"|&ndash;\n|align = \"center\"|&ndash;\n|align = \"center\"|&ndash;\n|-\n\n|\n|[[Joe Greene (Ontario politician)|Joe Greene]]\n|align = \"center\"|169\n|align = \"center\"|7.1%\n|align = \"center\"|104\n|align = \"center\"|4.4%\n|align = \"center\"|<br /><br /><br />29 <br /> '''<small>Eliminated after third ballot.</small>'''\n|align = \"center\"|1.2%\n|align = \"center\"|&ndash;\n|align = \"center\"|&ndash;\n|-\n\n|[[File:Allan MacEachen.jpg|50px]]\n|[[Allan MacEachen]]\n|align = \"center\"|165\n|align = \"center\"|6.9%\n|align = \"center\"|<br /><br /><br /><br />11<br /> '''<small>Eliminated after second ballot.</small>'''\n|align = \"center\"|0.5%\n|align = \"center\"|&ndash;\n|align = \"center\"|&ndash;\n|align = \"center\"|&ndash;\n|align = \"center\"|&ndash;\n|-\n\n|\n|[[Eric Kierans]]\n|align = \"center\"|<br /><br /><br />103 <br /> '''<small>Withdrew after first ballot.</small>'''\n|align = \"center\"|4.3%\n|align = \"center\"|&ndash;\n|align = \"center\"|&ndash;\n|align = \"center\"|&ndash;\n|align = \"center\"|&ndash;\n|align = \"center\"|&ndash;\n|align = \"center\"|&ndash;\n|-\n\n|\n|[[Harold Lloyd Henderson]]\n|align = \"center\"|<br /><br /><br />0 <br /> '''<small>Eliminated after first ballot.</small>'''\n|align = \"center\"|0.0%\n|align = \"center\"|&ndash;\n|align = \"center\"|&ndash;\n|align = \"center\"|&ndash;\n|align = \"center\"|&ndash;\n|align = \"center\"|&ndash;\n|align = \"center\"|&ndash;\n|-\n\n!colspan = \"2\"|Total\n!align = \"center\"|2,366\n!align = \"center\"|99.8%<sup>1</sup>\n!align = \"center\"|2,364\n!align = \"center\"|100.1%<sup>1</sup>\n!align = \"center\"|2,357\n!align = \"center\"|99.9%<sup>1</sup>\n!align = \"center\"|2,352\n!align = \"center\"|100.0%\n\n|-\n|align=\"center\" colspan=10|'''Source:'''  [http://www.cpac.ca/en/1968-liberal-convention/ CPAC - 1968 Liberal Convention]\n|}\n\n<sup>1</sup> Rounding error.\n\n== See also ==\n\n* [[Electoral history of Lester B. Pearson]]  - Trudeau's predecessor as leader of the Liberal Party and as Prime Minister.\n* [[Electoral history of Joe Clark]] - Trudeau's principal opponent in two general elections, alternating as Prime Minister.\n* 